    %h3.standout Portfolio
    %p The following work is in the public domain. Other client work can be viewed on request.
    %h4 SafariApps
    %p A hybrid mobile application for safari adventurers.
    %p
      The project began with a wireframing session with the client, and then quickly moved onto a rapid prototype, built with
      %a{:href => "http://www.sinatrarb.com/", :target => "_blank"} Sinatra
      and
      = succeed "." do
        %a{:href => "http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/", :target => "_blank"} Bootstrap
      The prototype is
      = succeed "," do
        %a{:href => "http://safariapps-prototype.heroku.com", :target => "_blank"} hosted on Heroku
      and the source code can be
      %a{:href => "https://github.com/fiznool/SafariApps-Prototype", :target => "_blank"} viewed on Gitub.
    %p
      The production app is currently in development; it is based on the
      %a{:href => "https://github.com/fiznool/mobile-backbone-boilerplate", :target => "_blank"} Mobile Backbone Boilerplate library
      and will be deployed as a hybrid app with
      = succeed "." do
        %a{:href => "http://phonegap.com", :target => "_blank"} PhoneGap
      The client is happy with the agile process, which involves regular builds being uploaded to Heroku for approval. The latest work-in-progress version of the app
      %a{:href => "http://safariapps.heroku.com", :target => "_blank"} can be seen here.
    %h4 SweepBook
    %p A Facebook app, developed with a friend to raise money for the 2011 Great North Run. App was built using Ruby on Rails and Twitter Bootstrap, and operates in standalone mode or is embedded within the Facebook chrome. Integrates with Facebook Graph API so that donators can be tagged and displayed on a donators page.
    %p
      See the
      %a{:href => "http://sweepbook.heroku.com/"} live app hosted on Heroku
      and
      %a{:href => "https://github.com/joewoodhouse30/SweepBook"} browse the source code on Github.
    %h3.standout Libraries
    %p
      All libraries are open source and can be found on
      = succeed "." do
        %a{:href => "http://github.com/fiznool"} Github
    %h4
      %a{:href => "https://github.com/fiznool/mobile-backbone-boilerplate", :target => "_blank"} Mobile Backbone Boilerplate
    %p A fork of the popular Backbone Boilerplate library, aimed at mobile devices. Used to develop SafariApps.
    %h4
      %a{:href => "https://github.com/fiznool/tappivate", :target => "_blank"} Tappivate
    %p
      A jQuery/Zepto plugin to make mobile web buttons and list views feel a bit more 'native'. Featured in
      = succeed "." do
        %a{:href => "http://javascriptweekly.com/archive/100.html"} JavaScript Weekly issue 100
    %h4
      %a{:href => "https://github.com/fiznool/oneliner", :target => "_blank"} OneLiner
    %p A jQuery/Zepto plugin to shrink text until it fits on one line. Developed for SafariApps to ensure that text in a mobile list view does not wrap to the next line.
    %h3.standout Community
    %h4 SWmobile
    %p 
      Organiser of
